where ρi is the ith singular value of UTV , commonly referred to as the ith principle angle between the subspaces of X and Y , θi. In above, we used the cyclic permutation property of the trace in the third and the fourth lines.
Since d2 is 1C Trace(R TR), it is always nonnegative, and it is only zero when the residual is zero, which is the case when span(X) = span(Y). Further, it is symmetric between U and V due to the form of (B.1) (singular values of V TU and V TU are the same). Also, d2 = 1C ∑C i=1 sin
2(θi), namely the average of the sines of the principle angles, which is a quantity between 0 and 1.
